b'The Dragon Boat Festival originates from China, and is known as the four major traditional festivals together with the Spring Festival, Ching Ming Festival and the Mid Autumn Festival of Han Chinese. Down the ages, Han Chinese row dragon boats and eat Zongzi (glutinous rice wrapped in bamboo leaves) on the Dragon Boat Festival. Zongzi in different regions have different flavors. Most people in Northern China like sweet Zongzi, while those in Southern China prefer salt ones. Do you prefer Zongzi with meat or Zongzi with red dates and sweet bean paste?  #Festivals #china #csair'
